What vitamins reduce cardiovascular disease? According to the American Heart Association, vitamin E is the only vitamin that reduces the risk of cardiovascular disease. Vitamin E is a fat-soluble vitamin that functions as an antioxidant. It protects cell membranes from oxidative damage and is important in the prevention of atherosclerosis, which is the build-up of plaque in the arteries. The American Heart Association recommends that adults consume 15 milligrams of vitamin E daily. Benefits of Vitamin E Vitamin
